	abstract = {LaTeX is widely used in academic publishing for its clean formatting and support for complex structures. However, converting manuscripts across various journal templates, such as IEEE, MDPI, and Springer, remains tedious, time-consuming, and error-prone. Existing manual and script-based methods are slow, rigid, and prone to formatting errors. In this study, we propose the LaTeX Format Converter (LaTeX-FC), a prompt-driven framework that leverages large language models (LLMs) such as Claude and Gemini to automate LaTeX format conversion. By using targeted prompts, LaTeX-FC preserves document structure and content while reducing manual effort. Experiments show it generalizes well across diverse templates. To our knowledge, this is the first approach to automate cross-template LaTeX conversion with LLMs, offering a scalable solution for researchers and publishers. The demo video and source code are publicly available on GitHub <sup>1</sup><sup>1</sup>https://github.com/ZoeLinUTS/ICDM-2025-LatexFC. © 2025 IEEE.},
